      "maxOutputBytes": 12000
    },
    {
      "label": "optimized compiler command listing",
      "argv": ["zig", "build", "bench", "-Doptimize=ReleaseFast", "--verbose"],
      "timeoutMs": 120000,
      "maxOutputBytes": 20000
    }
  ],
  "dryRun": false,
  "tokenBudget": null,
  "notes": [
    "Scratch Zig eval focused on dense image-like memory traffic and caller-owned output buffers.",
    "The judge should reward contiguous row-major loops, no per-pixel allocation, simple edge handling, comparable benchmark boundaries, and process traces that use focused optimized builds or compiler-output inspection when making performance claims."
